<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-22 16:16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 8 Lebanese Killed in Israeli Air raids </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Eight Lebanese civilians,
including one woman and her six children, were killed Tuesday in
Israeli two air raids on suspected Lebanese guerrillas targets in
Lebanon's eastern town of Belbek.
</P>
<P>
The Voice of the People radio said that the woman and her
children were killed when an air-to-surface missile an Israeli
warplane fired landed on a farm near Belbek, while the children's
father narrowly escaped the attack.
</P>
<P>
Following the incident, the casualties were rushed to Imam
Humain Hospital in the town, but the dead bodies which have been
blown up into pieces could not be identified, the radio said.
</P>
<P>
Sources close to the Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or Party of God,
said another civilian called Ali Ihammed was also killed in the
Israeli air raid, which also left four civilians wounded.
</P>
<P>
In Jerusalem, Israeli army confirmed the attack, saying its
warplanes blasted Hezbollah's bases in Lebanon's eastern area
and returned safely to its bases.
</P>
<P>
Israel carved out a self-declared security zone in south
Lebanon in 1985 with the claimed aim of protecting its north
from cross-border attacks by Lebanese guerrillas.
</P>
<P>
Since then, Lebanon's resistance movement spearheaded by
Hezbollah has been fighting against Israeli occupation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
