<HEADLINE> Iran Produces over 3.6 Million Tonnes of Steel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 22 (Xinhua) -- More than 3.6 million tonnes of
steel have been produced in the first eight months of this
Iranian year to end March 20, 1999, a senior Iranian official
announced on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Deputy head of the National Iranian Steel Company Mousa Aqaie
Lankarani told the Islamic Republic News Agency (IRNA) that the
output was 87 percent of the target for the period.
</P>
<P>
Out of the total 3.6 million tonnes of processed steel, hot
rolled sheets account for 30 percent, iron bars for 32 percent,
rods for 22 percent, cold rolled sheets for 14 percent and other
steel products for 2 percent.
</P>
<P>
Isfahan Steel Mill ranked the first by producing more than 1.3
million tonnes of processed steel while Mobarakeh Steel Complex
stood the second with an output of 1.1 million tonnes.
</P>
<P>
Iran had expected to produce some 6.7 million tonnes of steel
and to export 1.5 million tonnes during the current Iranian
year, officials said earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
The Minister of Mines and Metals Eshaq Jahangiri said
last month that Iran's annual steel output could reach
six million tonnes by the end of this Iranian year and steel
production is projected to touch 12 million tonnes annually by
the year 2002. 
</P>
</TEXT>
