<HEADLINE> Hamburg Police Find Another Mummified Body </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, December 22 (Xinhua) -- German police said Tuesday they
found the body of a man who had been dead in his apartment for
more than a year. This is the third time of the incident of its
kind in Hamburg in five weeks.
</P>
<P>
The Hamburg police spokesman Hans-Juergen Petersen said, the
man, 79-year-old pensioner, should die in September 1997, and would
die "probably from natural causes, because there is no evidence of
a crime".
</P>
<P>
The mummified body was discovered Monday after neighbors
called the fire department. They complained, there were always a
nasty smell coming from the apartment, Police reported.
</P>
<P>
In Hamburg, this northern German city, a bailiff found on
November 21 a 64-year-old Turk who had been lying dead in his
apartment for 18 months. Four days earlier, police called to
another flat discovered a 48-year-old man whose death went
unnoticed for five years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
