<HEADLINE> Turkish Police Seize 120 Kilograms of Hashish </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Turkish police Tuesday seized
120 kilograms of hashish in an anti-drug operation in eastern
Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Acting on a tip-off, the police found the drugs in Van
province linking neighboring Iran, otherwise the hashish would
have been transferred to western countries via Turkey, the
semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The police had detained six suspects involved in the case.
</P>
<P>
Turkish police seized over 10 tons of drugs including 5.348
tons of hashish and 3.766 tons of heroin in 2,928 operations
against drug smuggling by December 16 this year.
</P>
<P>
Police detained 5,172 Turkish people and 293 foreigners on
drug smuggling charges, and 15 smugglers were killed in clashes
with the police in the same period.
</P>
<P>
Turkey is on a transit route of drugs from the border areas of
Afghanistan and Pakistan to Europe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
