<HEADLINE> U.S. Federal Reserve Starts Meeting of Rate-setting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 22 (Xinhua)-- Policy-makers of the Federal
Open Market Committee started a meeting of rate-setting as
scheduled at 9 a.m. on Tuesday, the U.S. Federal Reserve said.
</P>
<P>
Most analysts expected the closed-door meeting of the
Committee--the central bank's top policy-making group-- would leave
U.S. interest rates unchanged after three rate cuts in the last
three months. They said that financial markets appeared happy with
what was shaping up to be a quiet end of the year. The Dow Jones
industrial average closed at 8,993.48 at 10 a.m. this morning.
</P>
<P>
It is expected that the meeting would make an announcement on
what is decided on borrowing costs at around 2:30 p.m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
