<HEADLINE> China, EU Sign First Research Cooperation Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, December 22 (Xinhua) -- China and the European Union
(EU) signed here Tuesday their first agreement for scientific and
techonological cooperation which is on the basis of cofinancing,
coparticipating, mutually sharing research results and protecting
intellectual property rights.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador to the European Community Song Mingjiang
said in his speech at the signing ceremony that this is an
important hallmark of the strengthening of the existing
cooperation between the two sides after 17 years of Sino-European
cooperation in science and technology.
</P>
<P>
It also marks the beginning of a new phase, in both scale and
level, in the cooperation of this area, Song said.
</P>
<P>
Over the past 17 years, both sides have already conducted
fruitful cooperation and exchanges, implementing over 230
cooperative projects in the fields of energy, information,
environment, health, agriculture, and biotechnology, the ambassador
said.
</P>
<P>
The agreement will lay the foundation for cooperation and joint
research in new and high technology areas, thus instill new
vitality into the development of Sino-European relations, Song
said.
</P>
<P>
About 50 people, including Chinese diplomats, the EU and its
member states' senior officials, attended the signing ceremony of
the agreement, which was signed by the Chinese ambassador, current EU
president, Austrian Minister of Science and Transport Caspar
Einem and EU Commissioner Edith Cresson, respectively on behalf of
the People's Republic of China, the European Union member states
and the European commission, the acting EU branch. 
</P>
</TEXT>
