<HEADLINE> Media Urged to Sensitize People on Dangers of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan media has been urged
to play a leading role in sensitizing the public on the dangers
of disasters.
</P>
<P>
The call was made Tuesday by Third Deputy Prime Minister and
Minister of Disaster Preparedness and Refugees Pau Etiang when
speaking during a consultative meeting to prepare for a regional
conference to be held in Nairobi in early 1999, Radio Uganda
reported Tuesday evening.
</P>
<P>
He encouraged journalists to specialize in disaster reporting,
adding that an information center is being developed for
journalists engaged in this kind of reporting.
</P>
<P>
The senior official also called on the general public to
assist the media in their effort to educate and disseminate the
right information on disasters.
</P>
<P>
He appealed to the private sector to sensitize their
communities on the need to prepare for any disaster.
</P>
<P>
The main task of his ministry is to try to develop a minimum
state of preparedness and a government policy on disaster is in
the offing, he added.
</P>
<P>
At the consultative meeting, he announced that four regional
and national seminars will be held for all stake-holders in
disaster management and preparedness from March to April next
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
