<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 3 Ugandans Lynched for Robbing Trader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Three people including a
police branch detective have been lynched by an enraged mob at
Mukono district, 30 kms east of Kampala, following a robbery of
40 million Shillings (40,000 U.S. Dollars) from a coffee trader.
</P>
<P>
The detective attached to Katwe Police Station with four
others waylaid the coffee trader Monday at Kisoga Lugogomo
village while returning from Greenland Bank, said a press release
issued Tuesday afternoon by the Police Headquarters.
</P>
<P>
The robbers traveling in a white Toyota Carina caused a
collision with the vehicle of the trader and in the scuffle that
ensued the robbers put the trader and his driver at gun point and
took away the money, ignition key and mobile phone, the press
release added.
</P>
<P>
As the robbers took off with their loots, they were blocked by
the mob at a village.  The robbers then opened fire and injured
two people and the mob later overpowered the robbers and lynched
three of them.
</P>
<P>
Inspector-General of Police John Cossy Odomel was quoted as
saying that he regretted the involvement of the detective in the
robbery, reiterating management determination to rid the force of
such personnel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
