TEHRAN -- A second stray missile from the U.S.-British strikes
against Iraq has been found in southern Iran, local daily Tehran
Times reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The two-meter-long cruise missile was found on the highway
between Khorramshahr to Ahvaz in Khuzstan province which borders
Iraq, the daily said.
</P>
<P>
Another missile landed in a residential area in downtown
Khorramshahr Thursday morning at the start of the U.S.-British
attack on Iraq, causing no injuries but some damages.
</P>
<P>
Iran has lodged a strong protest to both London and Washington
on Thursday by summoning British charge d'affaires in Tehran Nic
Browne and the Swiss ambassador, whose embassy looks after the
United States interest in Iran. (BC-Iran-Stray Missile)
</P>
