<HEADLINE> Iran, Oman Sign Memo on Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Oman and Iran signed a
memorandum of understanding Wednesday under which Oman will import
natural gas from Iran, the Islamic Republic News Agency (IRNA)
reported.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed by visiting Omani Minister of
Commerce and Industry Maqbool Bin Ali Bin Sultan and Iranian
Minister of Mines and Metals Eshaq Jahangiri at the end of the
sixth Tehran-Muscat joint economic commission session which
opened on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Under the deal, experts of the two countries will work on
details of the plan.
</P>
<P>
And Omani goods will be transported to the Commonwealth of the
Independent States (CIS) via Iran, especially through Iranian
free trade zones.
</P>
<P>
Iranian Mines and Metals Ministry is also to send a delegation
to Oman to survey copper industries in Oman and explore ways and
means for technical and engineering cooperation and investments.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, the two countries also discussed cooperation in
such areas as agriculture, veterinary affairs, fisheries, science
and research, post and telecommunications and mass media.
</P>
<P>
The trade relations between Iran and Oman are satisfactory,
said Jahangiri, but further steps are needed to take in this
respect and the joint economic commission is to facilitate such
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The Omani official, who arrived here Monday night, expressed
the hope that private sectors of Oman and Iran would become more
active in improving bilateral ties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
