<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Prices Remain Steady in November in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Inflation rate rose by 0.3 percent in November as compared
with the same month last year, while prices were down by 0.1
percent from September to November, said INSEE.
</P>
<P>
The main reason for the slowdown in inflation was the
continuous fall in energy prices, including those of oil
products, which dropped by 0.4-0.5 percent in November.
</P>
<P>
Household consumption rose by 0.1 percent in November, as
compared with a 0.9 percent fall in October.
</P>
<P>
The increase was attributed to a 7.5 percent growth in
automobile purchases as compared with October, and an increasing
purchase of pharmaceutical products by French families.
</P>
<P>
The survey also showed a drop of business confidence in
France, whose industrial activities have been slowing down for
months and are expected to continue to slow down for months.
</P>
<P>
Industrial leaders said that since the beginning of December,
all industrial sectors except automobile have been slowing down
their activities.
</P>
<P>
Industrial output by French enterprises is expected to
continue to decrease in the coming months along with falling
commodity prices, said INSEE. 
</P>
</TEXT>
