<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 23 (Xinhua) -- The former deputy director of
Jinan Customs has been given a life sentence by the Supreme
People's Court for participating in a smuggling racket.
</P>
<P>
Gao Qingting was also deprived of lifelong political rights and
also had part of his property confiscated.
</P>
<P>
A junior official in his department also received a three year
jail sentence for helping Gao.
</P>
<P>
The Intermediate People's Court of Jinan, capital of east
China's Shandong Province, found that Gao colluded with a Hong
Kong businessman in smuggling activities many times during his
term of office.
</P>
<P>
Instigated by Gao, Liu Guiliang, a customs officer, let 575
Swiss made watches, airfreighted from Hong Kong by the
businessman, pass through Jinan Customs without going through
declaration procedures between May and June of 1996, making a
total tariff loss of over 760,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
With the help of Gao, the Hong Kong businessman also flew more
than 47,000 sets of pager parts over the three months from
September to November of the same year, with a total tariff loss
of more than 3 million yuan.  
