activist killed himself in an unsuccessful attempt to blow up a
school bus full of Israeli school children in the Gaza Strip. The
attack came only six days after the signing of the Wye peace
accord in Washington.
</P>
<P>
Yassin's house arrest, which deeply angered his followers, was
one of the PNA's strongest steps against Hamas. At one point, in a
leaflet signed by its military wing, Hamas demanded Yasin's
release and made a rare direct threat against PNA Chairman Yasser
Arafat.
</P>
<P>
Yassin's release drew criticism from the Israeli government.
Moshe Fogel, Director of the Government Press Office, said the
PNA has to decide whether it wants to meet its commitments to
fight Hamas terror and move the peace process forward or turn a
blind eye to the terrorist activities of the Hamas leadership.
</P>
