<HEADLINE> Huge Funding for Key Projects in East China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, December 23 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong Province
has injected some 150 billion yuan into the construction of 92 key
projects so far this year, both figures all-time highs for the
province.
</P>
<P>
Money invested in projects already under construction stands at
25.5 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
To ensure that the economic growth rate goal can be achieved
this year, local authorities in Shandong nearly doubled the number
of projects and increased investment by 30 percent over the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
Most of the investment has been put into energy,
transportation, raw materials, the real estate sector, and urban
infrastructure construction, in which road construction projects
alone account for one-fifth of the total.
</P>
<P>
Improvement of the 11 waste-water treatment centers along
the Huaihe River and development of the Sanlianshun Lake community
and other residential areas are also key construction projects.
</P>
<P>
So far, a total of 17.8 billion yuan has been invested in 38
completed state and provincial key projects, accounting for 81.4
percent of this year's total investment plan.
</P>
<P>
Presently, most of the projects due to start operations by the
end of this year have been completed ahead of schedule or are
partially finished. These projects include the second phase of the
Qianwan project at the port of Qingdao, the automobile-parts
production project at Shandong First Auto Works, and the Xiaoqing
River water-treatment project. 
</P>
</TEXT>
