<HEADLINE> China to Hold 3rd International Airshow in 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 23 (Xinhua) -- China will hold the 3rd
International Airshow in Zhuhai, in south China's Guangdong
Province in the year 2000, official sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
Zhuhai Airshow is a State-level aviation and aerospace gala
with flight performance. It is jointly held by the General
Administration of Civil Aviation of China, Aviation Industries
Corp. of China, China Aerospace Corporation, and Zhuhai City
Government.
</P>
<P>
China is intended to invite aviation and aerospace leaders from
Russia, Canada, France, the United States, and Britain to attend
the event. Boeing and Airbus Industrie companies said earlier in
Zhuhai that they will participate in the next airshow with a even
larger scale after attending Airshow '98.
</P>
<P>
Zhuhai will further upgrade its apron and roads, local
officials said, adding that a four-storey news center, with a
floor space of nearly 8,000 square meters, were commissioned
during this year's airshow.
</P>
<P>
China's civil aviation will increase annually at a rate of
about ten percent, bringing a demand for 600 airliners in the next
two decades. The huge potentiality has attracted a growing number
of aircraft manufacturers to participate in Zhuhai Airshow.
</P>
</TEXT>
