<HEADLINE> Heavy Fog Disrupts Hefei Traffic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Heavy fog in Hefei, capital of
east China's Anhui Province, since Sunday has created hazardous
road and airport conditions.
</P>
<P>
Some 24 flights have been delayed during the last two days,
with some passengers stranded at the local airport.
</P>
<P>
Sections on the Hefei-Nanjing Expressway were closed, with no
serious traffic accidents recorded thanks to the efforts of local
highway departments.
</P>
<P>
Meteorologists attribute the heavy fog to the abrupt
temperature drop on December 20. 
