<HEADLINE> Philippines Customs Chief Fired </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph
Estrada Wednesday fired Customs Commissioner Pedro C. Mendoza in
connection with a gun-poking incident at Manila Hotel and replaced
him with Deputy Customs Commissioner Nelson Tan.
</P>
<P>
Estrada told a press conference that he received a report filed
by police that Mendoza pointed and poked his gun at several Manila
Hotel security officers and a 67-year-old lawyer.
</P>
<P>
Two of the security officers involved in the incident later
lodged a complaint against Mendoza to a police office.
</P>
<P>
"Because of this, I have now terminated the services of
Commissioner Mendoza," Estrada said.
</P>
<P>
Estrada said that although he values his family's close
relations with Mendoza, he cannot allow his personal feelings to
get in the way of his job. 
