<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Chief Executive Tung Chee
Hwa of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region said Wednesday
that the government will continue to work in cooperation with all
sectors of the community in creating a good business environment
in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Before attending a Christmas party for children at the
Government House here, Tung said a good environment conducive to
business and investment is very important to Hong Kong because
that is the way to ensure the recovery of the economy and to
create more jobs for the Hong Kong people.
</P>
<P>
Tung made the remarks in response to the media's inquiries
about a well!-known Hong Kong businessman's complaint about the
current business environment in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
"A harmonious community is fundamental to the creation of good,
attractive business environment, and I know that from that point
of view we will all work very hard to create this good
environment," Tung said.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's success has always been based on the rule of law
and this is also fundamental in attracting both Hong Kong people's
investment as well as overseas investment, Tung stressed.
</P>
<P>
"So from that point of view, it is important for all of us to
abide by the terms and conditions of contract," the chief
executive said. "Rule of law is fundamental to Hong Kong's
future," he added.
</P>
<P>
Tung said he is sure that the business community, as well as
the people in Hong Kong, whether they are in politics and whether
they are ordinary citizens, all love Hong Kong and will all work
very hard for a better tomorrow of Hong Kong. 
