<HEADLINE> Veteran Rojas Regains WBA Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Veteran Venezuelan Jesus Rojas
won his second career world champion after knocking out World
Boxing Association (WBA) super-flyweight titlist Satoshi Iida by
unanimous decision in Nagoya, Japan, on Wednesday,
</P>
<P>
Rojas, who briefly reigned in the WBA flyweight in 1989,
chased and battered the lefthanded Japanese with solid punching
and crafty clinchwork through out the 12-round bout, reports said.
</P>
<P>
Rojas stretched his record to 32 wins, 16 by knockout, against
seven losses and two draws. He remained unbeaten in five matches
against Japanese opponents.
</P>
<P>
For Iida, it was his third defence of the title wrested from
Yokthai Sith Oar of Thailand 12 months ago. It was his second
career defeat against 25 wins, including 11 KOs, and one draw.
