<DOCNO> XIE19981223.0119 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Farmers Taking Lead in Reforms (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Voters in Chinese cities are
in the process of electing people's deputies at the county-level,
with candidates appointed by the authorities.
</P>
<P>
Yet for China's urban voters direct elections still seem far
away, while their rural neighbors have long been accustomed to
electing village heads through popular choice.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, 90 percent of Chinese villages have adopted a
democratic financial system, in which, their leaders are obliged
to report to the community on the current financial status.
</P>
<P>
Wang Zhenyao, a doctorate candidate at Beijing University, a
specialist in rural democracy, says that the decade-old practice
of direct elections and an open financial system in China's
villages are actually quite democratic in the real sense.
</P>
<P>
Some Chinese observers point out that farmers have been an
important driving force behind the 20-year-old reforms. What's
more, they have been more or less taking the lead, compared with
their urban counterparts.
</P>
<P>
In late 1978, rural farmers in Xiaogang Village, in east
China's Anhui Province, risked imprisonment and maybe loss of
their lives, to break up the People's commune-owned farmland into
smaller plots so that they can farm on a household basis.
</P>
<P>
Indeed, this action instigated the rural reform in China and is
known as "the rural household contract responsibility system
linking income with output".
</P>
<P>
Urban reforms, mainly related to state-owned industries, were
started years later, but by then starvation and poor living
standards for a lot of rural inhabitants were things of the past,
thanks to earlier rural reform.
</P>
<P>
In the intervening years rural reforms have brought about a
dramatic cut in the income-gap between country folk and urban
residents. In 1984, the average annual per-capita income for urban
Chinese was only 1.9 times that of rural people, down from 2.6
times in 1978.
</P>
<P>
The booming township and village-based industries have changed
China's economic landscape completely as rural industries
contributed 27.7 percent of the gross domestic product in 1997,
compared with less than one percent 20 years ago.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981223.0120 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Farmers Taking Lead in Reforms (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Currently, some 210 million rural Chinese are employed by
township and village-based enterprises, preventing a huge influx
of unemployed rural laborers moving into big cities seeking
jobs, as was the case for many other countries on their way to
industrialization.
</P>
<P>
Nowadays, village elections, the household contract system and
rural industries are eulogized by some academics as "the Three
Great Creations" by Chinese farmers.
</P>
<P>
Chen Jiyuan, a researcher from the Rural Development Institute
of the Chinese Academy of Social Sciences, says that it is the
rural reform that has set an example for the ongoing reform drive
in the country as a whole.
</P>
<P>
Chinese farmers are known for being highly respectful about
education although pragmatic and sincere. According to official
figures, 60 percent of patented technologies available throughout
China have been bought by farmer-turned industrialists.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, banks say farmers make the most honest clients,
rarely taking on loans they cannot afford.
</P>
<P>
Nowadays, a large number of one-time farmers have become
successful entrepreneurs, some of whose companies have even won
international fame for their products.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that China now has over 80,000 farm produce
markets, with a yearly turnover of 1,500 billion yuan, and some 10
percent of farmers have joined marketing or servicing cooperatives
to increase their sales.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to the two-decade-old rural reform, the Chinese
government has successfully resolved the issues of feeding and
clothing its 1.2 billion-strong population, with the average
annual per-capita farm produce output actually exceeding the
world's level.
</P>
<P>
The fast development of the rural economy and the remarkable
increase in farmers' incomes have accelerated the integration
between cities and rural communities, which has helped China
achieve its ongoing sustainable development.
</P>
<P>
Nonetheless, some experts say that farmers are still facing
problems and that these need to be addressed. They refer to the
difficulty in marketing farm produce, and the resultant slow-down
in their income growth. This has led to increasing economic
burdens in the last few years.
</P>
<P>
The government should speed up the ongoing grain circulation
system restructuring and increase investment in agriculture, in a
bid to stimulate farmers' enthusiasm, the experts say. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981223.0121 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> First Non-government Nature Conservation Group 15 Years Old </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 23 (Xinhua) -- A seminar was held here today
to mark the 15th anniversary of the establishment of the National
Association of Wildlife Conservation of China.
</P>
<P>
Wang Fuxing, the association's secretary-general, told the
seminar that after 15 years of efforts the association, China's
first non-governmental organization for natural conservation,
has been developed into the largest nationwide wildlife
conservation organization in China.
</P>
<P>
Now, the association has more than 40,000 members and 100
branches all over China, Wang said, adding that it has also
established relations with more than 50 wildlife conservation
groups in 50 countries countries such as the United States,
Germany and Japan.
</P>
<P>
With the main purpose of raising awareness of wildlife
conservation in Chinese society, the association has hosted or
co-hosted some 30 national and international workshops, and has
trained more than 1,000 conservation workers in the past 15
years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
