<HEADLINE> ADB Helps Internet Development for Asia's Law Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Policy makers and law reformers
in Asia will have free and full access to an Internet library of
legislative materials with a 600,000-U.S.-dollar technical
assistant grant from the Asian Development Bank (ADB).
</P>
<P>
In a press statement issued here Wednesday, the ADB said that
the grant is aimed at assisting the bank's developing members in
the process of law reform by providing them with easy access to
full-text legislation and related materials in priority areas of
development law.
</P>
<P>
Current Internet resources covering full-text legislation and
related materials are widely scattered and not readily accessible,
despite an abundance of law-related sites and resources, the bank
said.
</P>
<P>
It said that the assistance is targeted at China, India,
Indonesia, Mongolia, Pakistan, the Philippines and Vietnam.
</P>
