<HEADLINE> Jordan Supports Call for Arab Summit on Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Jordan supports the call by
Yemen to hold an Arab summit over Iraq, Jordanian Information
Minister Nasser Judeh has said.
</P>
<P>
"Jordan always supports calls for holding an Arab summit and is
ready to participate in any Arab meeting for the benefit of the
Arab world," Judeh was quoted Wednesday as saying by the Jordan
Times.
</P>
<P>
The minister made the remarks after Arab League Secretary
General Ahmed Esmat Abdel-Meguid contacted foreign ministers of
the 22 AL member countries on the request by Yemen to hold an Arab
summit on the Iraqi issue.
</P>
<P>
However, Jordanian officials said privately that such a summit
was unlikely to be held due to opposition from Kuwait and Saudi
Arabia, foes of Iraq during the 1990 Gulf crisis triggered by
Iraq's invasion of Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
The summit, if held, would be the first since June 1996, shortly
after Benjamin Netanyahu's being elected Israeli prime minister
sparked fears among Arab countries that the peace process would be
set back. 
</P>
