<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hunan TV, Radio Company Sells Shares on Shenzhen Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Hunan TV and Radio Industrial
(Holdings) Co. Ltd. today sold 50 million shares on the Shenzhen
Securities Exchange at 9.18 yuan per share.
</P>
<P>
An official of the exchange said Hunan TV is the first
television production company in the country approved by the China
Securities Regulatory Commission to raise funds through the stock
market, raising 446.2 million yuan from today's transactions.
</P>
<P>
Most of these funds will be used to import advanced equipment,
including a digital production system and equipment for shooting
and editing TV programs, said a company executive.
</P>
<P>
The company will also spend more than 60 million yuan
purchasing and upgrading the existing cable television network in
the city of Changsha, the provincial capital of Hunan.
</P>
<P>
As TV sets become more common in homes all across the country,
television advertising revenues continue to increase
sharply. Statistics show that about 80 percent of all advertising
spending goes into TV ads.
</P>
<P>
TV ads are also a major source of income for Hunan TV and Radio
Company, which last year earned 168 million yuan from these
ads. The company has now gained a 50-percent share of Hunan
Province's advertising market.
</P>
<P>
Hunan TV and Radio Company produces some 600 TV dramas and
other programs annually, accounting for 45 percent of Hunan
Province's total. Sixty percent of the TV programs now being seen
in the province are produced by the company, according to a
company executive. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
