<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Plans To Reform Social Science Academy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 23 (Xinhua) -- China released its plan here
today for reforming the Chinese Academy of Social Sciences (CASS)
to create a responsibility system.
</P>
<P>
It means that researchers' incomes will be linked to their
academic record to some extent, and institutes will have greater
decision-making power.
</P>
<P>
There will also be an attempt to raise funds from different
sources instead of mainly relying on government funding.
</P>
<P>
Contacts with foreign academia will be encouraged and the
number of academic committees at both the academy and institute
levels will be increased.
</P>
<P>
The academy will also dismiss unqualified researchers. Since
1977, when CASS was established, it has had an "iron rice bowl"
system, where researchers get equal pay no matter what they do.
</P>
<P>
The reform will also make CASS's logistics departments
independent entities or companies to compete in the market. And,
researchers will no longer qualify for entirely free medical care
and housing.
</P>
<P>
Observers say that the reforms will make the 4,000-person
institute more vigorous as it tries to become an authentic academy
with international influence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981223.0166 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Number Of Mobile Phone Users Increasing In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 23 (Xinhua) -- China had 22.63 million mobile
telephone users by the end of November, according to the Ministry
of Information Industry (MII).
</P>
<P>
This was an increase of 71 percent from the beginning of the
year. From January to June, 910,000 new mobile phone users signed
up every month, compared to a monthly average of 480,000 in 1997.
</P>
<P>
China has given priority to mobile communications since they
were introduced into the country a decade ago. The number of
mobile phone users has been growing at an annual rate of 150
percent.
</P>
<P>
China took ten years to get the first ten million, but only 17
months to add an additional ten million people by September of
this year.
</P>
<P>
More than 60 percent of China's mobile phone users use digital
phones. They can reach 19 countries and regions.  
</P>
</TEXT>
