<HEADLINE> China's Social Science Program For 21st Century </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Li Tieying, president of the
Chinese Academy of Social Sciences (CASS), said today that one of
the major goals of China's social sciences in the 21st century is
to help create a just and reasonable international order.
</P>
<P>
Li said at the Academy's annual meeting that researchers should
do their best to help create a good international environment for
China's social and economic development.
</P>
<P>
He said that major research subjects will include a study of
the World Trade Organization, international trade disputes, and
international finance. The researchers are expected to provide
suggestions for China's international strategies.
</P>
<P>
Another important question is how the information revolution,
especially the "knowledge-based economy", will affect China's
economic and social structure and people's lives, Li said.
</P>
<P>
"It is impossible for China to make decisions in a scientific
and democratic way if no attention is paid to social sciences," he
stressed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
