<HEADLINE> Cambodian Caloric Intake, Lowest in Region </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The average of Cambodians' daily caloric intake is 1,980
calories, the Cambodia Daily reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Average daily intake for the entire East and Southeast Asia
region (not including Japan) is 2,740 calories.
</P>
<P>
The main reason for the low caloric intake is poverty. It was
reported that 36 percent of Cambodians are living in poverty.
</P>
<P>
According to a survey, Phnom Penh residents need 1,378 riel
(about 0.36 U.S. dollar) per day to buy food to meet the 1,980
calorie level. 
</P>
</TEXT>
