<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Settling Question Of Nationality Of Macao Residents (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 23 (Xinhua) -- China plans to deal with the
question of the nationality of the residents of Macao in a
flexible way that does not violate the basic principles of China's
Nationality Law, to maintain Macao's prosperity and stability,
according to Zhang Chunsheng, deputy director of the Standing
Committee of the National People's Congress's Legislative Work
Committee.
</P>
<P>
Zhang was explaining a draft of China's Nationality Law in the
Macao Special Administrative Region (SAR) to the sixth meeting of
the NPC Standing Committee today.
</P>
<P>
The draft was submitted to the NPC Standing Committee today for
examination, with suggestions by the NPC Preparatory Committee for
the Macao SAR.
</P>
<P>
It says that all Macao residents of Chinese descent who were
born on Chinese territory (including Macao) and those who meet the
requirements of China's Nationality Law are Chinese citizens
weather they hold a Portuguese travel certificate and identity
card or not.
</P>
<P>
People of both Chinese and Portuguese descent can choose
Chinese or Portuguese citizenship freely, but only one.
</P>
<P>
So, before choosing their citizenship, Macao SAR residents
enjoy the rights set forth in the Macao SAR Basic Law before
choosing citizenship, but not rights restricted by the
nationality.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
