<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Settling Question of Nationality of Macao Residents (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Zhang says that it is absolutely necessary to explain the
citizenship issue at an early stage because of a number of issues
like qualifications of the Chief Executive of the Macao SAR and
leading government officials, the chairman and vice-chairmen of
the Legislative Council, the president of the court of final
Appeal, and deputies to the NPC in the Macao SAR, SAR visas, and
the identity of Macao permanent residents, and the definition of
the identity of Chinese citizens in Macao in accordance with the
Nationality Law.
</P>
<P>
He says that the draft states that Macao residents of both
Chinese and Portuguese blood can not be Chinese citizens naturally
before choosing citizenship.
</P>
<P>
The freedom to choose citizenship reflects the principle of
flexibility that is conducive to the smooth transition and
transfer of power in Macao, Zhang says.
</P>
<P>
The draft also states that Chinese citizens in Macao with
Portuguese travel documents and residence rights in other
countries can travel to other countries and regions with the
proper documents but in the Macao SAR and other parts of China do
not have their rights protected by Portuguese and other foreign
consulates because they hold such documents.
</P>
<P>
The more than 100,000 Chinese citizens in Macao who hold
Portuguese passports, Zhang says, are not recognized by the
Chinese Government in their Portuguese citizenship and if they do
not want to choose Chinese citizens, they can give it up after the
Macao SAR is founded.
</P>
<P>
The draft also says that Macao residents who are Chinese
citizens returning from overseas before or after the founding of
the SAR can apply for a change of citizenship at Macao SAR
departments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
