<HEADLINE> Sharp Increase In China's Offshore Oil Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 23 (Xinhua) -- The China National Offshore
Oil Corp (CNOOC) expects to produce 16.4 million tons of crude oil
by the end of this year in a continued increase in offshore oil
production for five consecutive years.
</P>
<P>
According to a senior CNOOC official, it has made an effort to
maintain offshore oil production amidst dropping oil prices and
production. The country has given priority to offshore oil
exploration this year and has invited foreign cooperations in oil
and gas exploration in the South China Sea, East China Sea and
Yellow Sea.
</P>
<P>
CNOOC has signed more than 130 oil contracts and agreements
with at least 70 oil companies from 18 countries and regions, with
total foreign investment amounting to 6.4 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The official says that CNOOC has had an astonishing 80 percent
success rate in offshore wildcat drilling this year, and expects
to find an additional 130 million tons of proven oil reserves and
10 billion cu.m. of proven gas reserves by the end of this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
