<HEADLINE> 20 Killed in Bus Collision in S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Twenty people were
killed and 19 others seriously injured in the early hours of
Wednesday when a bus collided with a heavy-duty truck in Western
Cape, South African Press Association (SAPA) reported.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred shortly after midnight on a highway
about 30 kilometers outside Laingsburg, some 250 kilometers
northeast of Cape Town, SAPA quoted police spokesman Mark Collins
as saying.
</P>
<P>
Collins said the bus was carrying about 80 passengers at the
time of the accident. About 40 had sustained light injuries and
were treated at the scene.
</P>
<P>
The driver of the truck was killed but his assistant escaped
unhurt.
</P>
<P>
He said 14 of the 19 seriously injured passengers were taken
to the Laingsburg Hospital. Seven were later transferred by
air force helicopter to the No.1 City Hospital at Goodwood and the
Tygerburg Hospital in Bellville. 
</P>
</TEXT>
