<HEADLINE> China to Secure Another Bumper Harvest in 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 23 (Xinhua) -- China expects to maintain
grain output at 490 million tons, this year's total, or above next
year, said
</P>
<P>
Minister of Agriculture Chen Yaobang at a press conference
here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Chen said cotton output will be about 3.5 million tons in 1999,
lower than the 4.2 million tons for this year.
</P>
<P>
He said that output of meat, marine products, and other farm
produce will be increased steadily next year.
</P>
<P>
Chen added that China plans to raise the growth rate of
farmers' net per capita income to four percent next year from this
year's three percent.
</P>
<P>
In 1999, China will lift ten million rural residents above the
poverty line, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that in order to achieve these goals, China will adopt
such measures as reform, restructuring products, enhancing
township enterprises, developing infrastructure, protecting the
environment and promoting technological innovation. 
</P>
