<HEADLINE> Sino-Arabian Chemical Fertilizer Company Record Output </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINHUANGDAO, December 23 (Xinhua) -- The Sino-Arabian Chemical
Fertilizer Co. Ltd. of Qinhuangdao in Hebei Province has produced
700,000 tons of chemical fertilizers so far this year.
</P>
<P>
This exceeds the company's designed production capacity by 45.8
percent. Last year, it produced 600,000 tons of chemical
fertilizers, 25 percent more than the designed production
capacity, a company spokesman says.
</P>
<P>
Sino-Arabian Chemical Fertilizer is a joint venture with
Tunisia and Kuwait, built at a cost of 58 million U.S. dollars to
producing nitrogenous, phosphate, and potash fertilizers.
</P>
<P>
The company has become a leader in efficient compound phosphate
fertilizer in China after more than a decade of development.
</P>
<P>
Its products sell well all over China and are exported to other
parts of Asia. It expects to have 1.2 billion yuan in sales this
year, a sharp increase from last year.  
</P>
