<HEADLINE> Kopke to Leave Marseille for Nuremberg </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Andreas Kopke, Germany's former
goalkeeper, got the green light on Tuesday to leave French club
Olympique Marseille and would join Bundesliga's Nuremberg.
</P>
<P>
Kopke agreed to play for the Bundesliga club until June 30,
2001. No transfer fee was revealed.
</P>
<P>
