<HEADLINE> Myanmar to Add Nine More Entry Points for Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar is planning to add nine
more entry points along the border in five states and divisions
for world tourists and will allow them to visit inland far up to
the capital and leave from any point.
</P>
<P>
According to a latest issue of the local "Advertisement and
Procurement Directory" journal, the entry points to be added are
Lwaigyai, Muse, Chinshwehaw, Mongla, Tachilek, Myawaddy, Phaya
Thonzu, Kalein Aung and Kawthaung in Kachin, Shan, Kayin, Mon and
Tanintharyi states and divisions respectively.
</P>
<P>
The move is aimed at absorbing more foreign tourists from
neighboring countries to visit Myanmar, further promoting the
development of the country's tourism and the earning of foreign
exchange.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar has also opened to tourists more new sites such as
Sittwe, Mrauk Oo, Kyaikhtiyo, Myitkyina, Pathein and Chaungtha
Beach.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, the number of foreign
tourists visiting Myanmar reached 567,458 in the 1997-98 fiscal
year which ended in March, of which, 302,336 entered through
border points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
