<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka to Launch Master Plan for Rural Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka is to implement a
ten year master plan for rural industrial development from January
1999, the official Daily News reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
For the past nine months the Ministry of Vocational and Rural
Industrial Development has been preparing this plan in
collaboration with the United Nations Development Program and the
International Labor Organization, the reports quoted a ministry
spokesman as saying.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the ministry has been conducting a project
which included a survey on rural industrial potential and
preparation of this master plan.
</P>
<P>
The survey team selected a sample of 2,000 small and medium
scale industries and conducted a detailed sample survey in
ascertaining the specific nature of strengths, weaknesses and
constraints and problems of entrepreneurs, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
There are 50 project files on selected industries which would
be useful for entrepreneurs who wish to embark on such industries,
the spokesman said, adding the project and survey has also
collected data and conducted meetings with entrepreneurs of all
districts in the country.
</P>
<P>
The secondary data such as existing population and industrial
enterprises of small and medium scale in each district has also
been ascertained, the reports added. 
</P>
