<HEADLINE> Mexico, US Sign Satellite Communications Pact </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Mexico and the United
States on Tuesday signed a protocol on the transmission and
reception of satellite signals, official sources said.
</P>
<P>
Under the pact, Mexico will use its available technology to
include national coverage and emergency services in its
concessions, the Communications and Transports Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
The pact, included in the two countries' free trade agreement,
will also allow companies with U.S. capital to widen their range
of services with the authorization of the Mexican government.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed by Mexican Communications Ministry
representative Jorge Nicolin and Vonya McCann, who heads the US
State Department's communications policy and international
information. 
