<HEADLINE> Coordinated Transportation Between Cities Of Xi'an And Qingdao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, December 23 (Xinhua) -- Xi'an, in Shaanxi Province in
northwest China, now uses the same customs procedures as other
border ports thanks to a coordinated transportation railway and
ocean shipping system linked to Qingdao, a port city in east
China.
</P>
<P>
A cargo management center for Xi'an Customs has been set up at
Xi'an's east railway station so that agents can fill out customs
declarations and go through procedures for ocean shipment at Xi'an
Customs and cargo from abroad can be delivered directly to Xi'an
via Qingdao Port.
</P>
<P>
The center also has a 1,500-square-meter warehouse close to the
station.  
