<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The United States opposes any effort to lift
economic sanctions against Iraq and would use its veto power in
the U.N. Security Council to keep them in place, the White House
said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"We certainly oppose any effort to dismantle the sanctions
regime and if it meant using our veto, we would," White House
spokesman Joe Lockhart told reporters.
</P>
<P>
