priority even after the Washington Summit in 1999, and also its
enlargement, Klaus Naumann, chairman of the NATO Military
Committee said here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with Romania's Prime Minister Radu Vasile,
Klaus Naumann, now on a visit to Romania, stressed the important
role played by Romania as NATO's partner that went beyond the
Partnership for Peace (PfP)and said interoperability between
Romanian Armed Forces and NATO forces was an essential criterion
in assessing Romania's admission request. (Romania-NATO)
</P>
<P>
