<HEADLINE> One Woman Injured in Church Bomb Blast in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 22 (Xinhua) -- A young woman was injured
slightly in a bomb blast in a church in Pakistan's biggest city of
Karachi on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The explosion, which took place in St. Patrick's Cathedral in
the commercial area of Saddar at 6:00 p.m. local time (1:00 p.m.
GMT), caused no other casualties, the Associated Press of Pakistan
(APP) reported.
</P>
<P>
The woman was injured by stones that were thrown by the
explosion waves.
</P>
<P>
The bomb, a time-device with low intensity, was planted below a
bench at the tail end of the church hall, Moinuddin, chief of the
bomb disposal squad, was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The blast occurred at the 130-year-old church at the end of a
sermon which was attended by around 90 people, APP said.
</P>
<P>
No one has claimed responsibility for the bombing so far and
investigations are underway, APP said. 
</P>
