<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania's President Signs Government's New Structure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Romania's President Emil
Constantinescu signed into law the new structure of the Romanian
Government, according to a press release published Tuesday by the
Press Office of the Presidency.
</P>
<P>
The new structure of the government was lodged by Prime
Minister Radu Vasile and passed by the parliament on December 16.
</P>
<P>
Under its new structure, the government consists of 18 members,
with 7 members less. As a result, the government has become
stripped of Ministers of Privatization, Communications, Reform,
Tourism, Research and Technology as well as Minister for the
Relations with Parliament and Secretary of State to the Defense
Ministry.
</P>
<P>
According to the Prime Minister, the governmental revamp was
the first stride toward the reform of the central administration
and one of the conditions requested ahead of the European
integration. He also said that by shrinking the government he
hoped to curtail budgetary spending. 
</P>
</TEXT>
