<HEADLINE> First German Bundesliga Club Forms Registered Company </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Borussia Moenchengladbach became
Tuesday the first German Bundesliga club to form a share-holding
company, the Media here reported.
</P>
<P>
However the highly-indebted club has restricted the registered
company solely to the construction and operation of a new stadium.
</P>
<P>
The team, badly adrift at last place in the 18-team league,
will not initially be part of the company. Any later move to
include the team will need the approval of the general meeting of
the members. 
