<HEADLINE> Fanz Gets Frankfurt Coaching Job </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, December 22 (Xinhua) -- German Bundesliga club Eintracht
Frankfurt Tuesday appointed 44-year-old Reinhold Fanz as the club
coach.
</P>
<P>
Fanz moves from second division Hanover and succeeds Horst
Ehrmantraut who was dismissed by Frankfurt on December 8.
</P>
<P>
Ehrmantraut led Frankfurt to promotion last season but the
team is struggling at fourth from bottom in the 18-team league.
</P>
<P>
Fanz, who played in the Bundesliga for Fortuna Duesseldorf and
Karlsruhe, has been given a contract until the end of June 2000.
</P>
<P>
"He was the man our president wanted a year ago," said
Frankfurt manager Gernot Rohr.
</P>
<P>
"He is the right man and fits in here. We are all relieved
that we have managed to agree the deal before Christmas."
</P>
