<DOCNO> XIE19981223.0284 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 1998, Year of Reforming Romanian Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, December 22 (Xinhua) -- The year 1998 is for the
Romanian Education Ministry a year when "comprehensive reform
measures were taken for all education levels in Romania," said a
Romanian Education Ministry official Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Director of Public Relations Directorate in the Education
Ministry Mircea Muresan made the statement in an interview with
the national Rompres news agency.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the landmarks of the Romanian education reform
that turned into reality in 1998, Muresan mentioned the curricula,
syllabuses and textbooks. He spoke about the relaunch of
scientific research in universities, the improvement of the
infrastructure, the reform of school and academic management
through decentralization and the institutional autonomy of the
education units, and advanced forms of international cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The Education Ministry was reorganized in 1998, he said, adding
that contests were held for more than 180 posts. The reform of
vocational education started, in cooperation with small and
medium-sized units, as well as the reform of colleges that train
school masters and of high sanitary schools. Programs were applied
for giving fresh impetus to the study of widely spoken languages,
classical languages, sport and arts in secondary and high schools.
</P>
<P>
The private school network extended considerably in 1998 and
the university management reform resulted in university autonomy,
he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981223.0285 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IMF Okays Third Annual ESAF Loan for Armenia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 22 (Xinhua) -- The International Monetary
Fund (IMF) Tuesday announced the approval of the third annual loan
for Armenia under the Enhanced Structural Adjustment Facility
(ESAF), totaling about 59 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The loan, which has been increased by some 11 million dollars,
will be used to support the government's economic program for
1999. The loan is available in two equal semiannual installments
of about 29 million dollars, the first of which is made available
at the end of December, this year.
</P>
<P>
The major objectives of Armenia's development strategy are to
address the spillover effects of the Russian crisis while trying
to move forward in consolidating the gains achieved so far in
stabilization and deepening structural reform. The government
program is designed to achieve the real annual GDP growth of at
least 5.5 percent in 1998 and 4.0 percent in 1999. End-period
inflation is targeted at single-digits in both years.
</P>
<P>
The total commitment under the three-year loan is thus
increased to the equivalent of about 154 million dollars for the
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981223.0286 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-23 </DATE_TIME>
