<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IDB Finances Private Sector Toll Road in Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 22 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank (IDB) Tuesday announced the approval of 130
million U.S. dollars in financing for private sector toll road
linking Sao Paulo with Sorocaba and Aracoiaba da Serra.
</P>
<P>
The financing is provided to Concessionaria de Rodovias do
Oeste de Sao Paulo to support the construction, upgrade,
operation, and maintenance of approximately 156 kilometers of toll
road between the three cities.
</P>
<P>
The project is expected to reduce travel time in the concession
area from 50 percent to 80 percent and decrease fuel consumption
and vehicle operating costs due to smoother traffic flow and
improved roadway quality.
</P>
<P>
The IDB financing consists of a loan of up to 75 million
dollars from the Bank's ordinary capital and a loan of some 55
million dollars from funds provided by syndicated commercial
banks. The IDB resources represent the first international
financing for a state toll road project in the state of Sao Paulo.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
